# BirdNET-Go base URL (REQUIRED).
# In production the nginx container proxies /api/ here, resolved at container
# start. In dev the Vite proxy uses the same value. Point it at your instance:
BIRDNETGO_URL=http://192.168.1.10:8080
#
# This must be reachable FROM INSIDE the container, and its host is forwarded to
# the upstream as the Host header (+ SNI for https). A LAN IP is simplest. A
# hostname works too, including one fronted by a reverse proxy or Cloudflare
# Tunnel that routes by Host/SNI. When BirdNET-Go also runs in Docker on this
# host, the cleanest option is to put Saezuri on its network and use the service
# name + internal port (e.g. http://birdnet-go:8080) — traffic stays local, no
# DNS, no round-trip out to Cloudflare. See docker-compose.yml for how.

# Optional auth token for a BirdNET-Go instance running with Security.PrivateMode.
# nginx injects it as an "Authorization: Bearer <token>" header on proxied /api/
# calls; the browser never receives it. Leave unset for public LAN instances.
# BIRDNETGO_TOKEN=
